reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice and sturdy shelf unit! Fairly easy to assemble!
reviews.reviewText: It’s a sturdy and perfect for a small space unit!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Decent, doesn't cost much, good to capture the mess of kids shoes
reviews.reviewText: Not big enough to hold boots but good for regular flat shoes. I notice other reviewers say the shelves are the wrong length, that is because the diagram in the instructions are wrong. If you ignore the diagram and just build it to be square shelves joined by poles it comes together easily. I actually had the kids make it as a snowy day project and it went smoothly. The actual shelves are a polyester fabric so again, won't hold heavy boots but good for regular shoes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Best shoe rack ever! It’s cheap but doesn’t make my closet look cheap. I bought 5!!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Fabric shelves are saggy
reviews.reviewText: Followed instructions but fabric shelves ended up drooping downward. There's too much fabric based on how these are supposed to be put together. Doesn't match picture.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Missing pieces is consistent
reviews.reviewText: I read a few reviews that stated they were missing pieces but i decided to buy it anyways. I can't finish the last shelf or put the finisher on top. I dont have the last "shelf"paper and I'm missing 3 connectors, 1 short, and 1 long pole. The dimensions is exactly what im looking for though. The "shelves" that hold the shoes is like a construction paper felt. Idk how long they will last and I'm not sure what to replace them with yet but for now hopefully it should last awhile before thats needed. 😅 It took about 25mins to put together. It does its job.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Bought this thinking it would be wobbly and I’d have to anchor to wall at various points. Frame is metal and strong. Made well and fits my space perfectly.
